# Lambda Handler Rules

## Organization
- `lambda/` contains **only handler functions** — one handler per file
- Business logic lives outside `lambda/` (e.g., `src/services/`, `src/utils/`)
- Handlers are thin wrappers that orchestrate calls to other modules

## Folder Structure
```
src/
  lambda/
    feature-name/
      feature-trigger.ts
      feature-ingestion.ts
    api/
      get-resource.ts
      update-resource.ts
  services/
    feature-name/
      feature-service.ts
  utils/
    validators.ts
```

## Response Format
**Always use `buildResponse`** from `src/utils/response.ts`. Never manually construct `{ statusCode, headers, body }`.

```typescript
import { buildResponse } from '../../utils/response';

// ✅ Success
return buildResponse(200, true, 'Operation completed successfully', { data });

// ✅ Error
return buildResponse(500, false, 'Operation failed', { error: (error as Error).message });
```

## Documentation
Every new Lambda handler must be documented in `docs/LAMBDA_FUNCTIONS.md` with:
- Purpose, trigger, timeout, memory, business logic location
